The inner apartment, next to the room in which the festivities were going on, was again oc- cupied by the Czarewicz and the Czar’s sister Nathalia; thence they saw the daneing and all the gay tumult, the curtains with which the place was most handsomely decorated being drawn a little and they were only seen through a lattice by the guests. The natural beauty of the Czarewiez was wonder- fully shown off by his civilized German dress and powdered wig. Nathalia was escorted by the creme of the married ladies. This day, too, beheld a great departure from Russian manners, which up to this forbade the female sex from appearing at public as- semblies of men, and from festive gayeties‚ for some were not only allowed to be at the dinner, but also at the daneing afterwards.
